Laws Ch. 223 (Former H.B. 247); states, in part, that certain property insurance contracts may not require that an action for a claim under the contract be filed less than one (1) year from the date of the denial of the claim by the insurer. However, property insurance contracts may permit an action for a claim made under the contract to be filed more than one (1) year from date of denial of the claim by the insurer.
